snippet.textDisplay: The black wedding dress story grabbed me because my Grandmother (who was an English War Bride for an American farm boy who went off to fight WWII and was stationed in London) wore a black wedding dress.  White fabric was rationed for uniforms, hospitals...The War.  It was very bad form to use anything that was needed for the war effort not to mention those things were harder to get.  So Grandma went in the other direction and had a black wedding dress with a black spanish veil.  She liked the drama.  The marriage turned out fine, btw and 5 children and more grandchildren resulted.  So don't be scared.  Congratulations!!!!!!!!
